  }))))), mdx("p", null, "My daily work looks very basic: List -> Action -> Articulate."), mdx("p", null, "A lot of my time is spent in data discovery, rapid prototyping the first MVP, and writing Design docs (Thanks to Eugene for structuring content on writing a great ", mdx("a", {
    parentName: "p",
    "href": "/resources/ml-design-docs/"
  }, "design doc"), ". I use this design doc for alignment.  We work in a very Agile structure with the Product team. Most of my time goes in aligning with Product Managers, Developers, devops and design for  scoping and defining success metrics for a given project. It\u2019s an amazing way to collaborate end to end on how the final product would look like. "), mdx("p", null, "This process enables all the stakeholders to align on a single vision and gives the ability to experiment without going outside the scope hence getting projects LIVE in shorter durations."), mdx("p", null, "I enjoy writing/ideating equally as I enjoy writing code. That helps in articulating complex ideas into simpler action points for all team members to understand.  Here is a blog I ", mdx("a", {
